!!Unix Time
Typically, time is measure on computers using [[Unix time|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix_time]].
The Unix epoch (or Unix time or POSIX time or Unix timestamp)
is the number of seconds that have elapsed since
January 1, 1970 (midnight UTC/GMT),
not counting leap seconds.
Literally speaking the epoch is Unix time 0 (midnight 1/1/1970),
but 'epoch' is often used as a synonym for 'Unix time'. 

