!!NIST Randomness Beacon
Since early evening on September 5^^th^^, 2013
the US National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST)
has been
[[publishing a 512-bit, full-entropy random number every minute of every day|https://beacon.nist.gov/home]].
Each number is cryptographically signed so that you can easily verify that it was generated by the NIST.
A date stamp is included in the process,
so that you can tell when the random values were created.
In addition, all of the values are linked to the previous value
in a chain so that you can detect if any of the past numbers
in the series have been altered after the next number is published. 